<TITLE> DCC unveils Tk 1,400 cr budget </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com)Mayor Sadeque Hossain Khoka on Monday unveiled a Tk 1,400 crore budget for Dhaka City Corporation for the fiscal year 2009-2010. The authorities plan to earn Tk 603 crore in revenue and spend Tk 1,020 crore on development. They also target government block allocation and special allocation worth Tk 200 crore and another Tk 540 crore from public-private partnership project and foreign assistance. In the last fisca year, the DCC had a Tk 1,009 crore budget, which was revised at Tk 872 crore. The DCC now has debts worth Tk 240 crore. At a press conference, the mayor said they did not hike the tax rate from existing 12 percent but the coverage would be widened. Khoka proposed DCC secretariat to be put under the prime minister's office for better coordination among the offices. He also proposed more positions of deputy mayor to add pace to the works. b
